Brougham Hall Chapel, United Kingdom 🏴󠁧󠁢󠁥󠁮󠁧󠁿🇬🇧
.
.
.
Built in the 14th century and has a fascinating history. Rescued from dereliction in 1985, today it is one of the largest country house restoration projects in England and is home to an array of arts and craft workshops and businesses. The chapel was build in 1310.
.
.

Castlerigg Stone Circle, Lake District, United Kingdom 🏴󠁧󠁢󠁥󠁮󠁧󠁿🇬🇧
.
.
.
Castlerigg is perhaps the most atmospheric and dramatically sited of all British stone circles, with panoramic views and the mountains of Helvellyn and High Seat as a backdrop.
It is also among the earliest British circles, raised in about 3000 BC during the Neolithic period.
.
.
.
